Title: Note on the Off-Shell Equivalence between the Linear and Non-Linear

Sigma ModelsComments: 16 pages, plain TeX, uses harvmac, with 2 eps figures

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B490 (1997) 457-471

As is well known, one can arrange the parameters of the O(N) non-linear sigmamodel to reproduce the low energy S-matrix elements of the renormalizable O(N)linear sigma model. In this note we provide details which are necessary inorder to obtain the off-shell equivalence between the two theories.